Ban said at a conference on Wednesday that he intends to meet with foreign ministers from five permanent countries in the Council - the USA, Russia, China, England and France - on the margins of the ministerial session of the General Assembly to discuss Syria.
Ban expressed his regret that the divisions in the Council and between the Syrian people and regional powers "made this situation unresolved".
Ban asked the five permanent members to demonstrate the solidarity and unity shown when they were able to conclude an agreement on Iran's nuclear weapons, thus addressing the Syrian crisis.
